nkit:name":"googleai/gemini-2.5-flash","genkit:output":"{\"custom\":{\"candidates\":[{\"content\":{\"parts\":[{\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"title\\\": \\\"Dairy-Free Roasted Vegetable Pasta\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"A wholesome and flavorful pasta dish featuring a vibrant medley of roasted vegetables tossed with a rich, dairy-free tomato sauce. This recipe is perfect for a satisfying meal that caters to dairy restrictions without compromising on taste.\\\",\\n  \\\"prepTime\\\": \\\"20 minutes\\\",\\n  \\\"cookTime\\\": \\\"40 minutes\\\",\\n  \\\"servings\\\": 4,\\n  \\\"ingredients\\\": [\\n    \\\"1 lb (450g) pasta of your choice (e.g., penne, spaghetti)\\\",\\n    \\\"2 tbsp olive oil, plus more for serving\\\",\\n    \\\"1 large bell pepper (any color), cored and chopped into 1-inch pieces\\\",\\n    \\\"1 medium zucchini, chopped into 1-inch pieces\\\",\\n    \\\"1 pint (about 2 cups) cherry tomatoes\\\",\\n    \\\"1 red onion, chopped into wedges\\\",\\n    \\\"4 cloves garlic, peeled and smashed\\\",\\n    \\\"1 (28 oz) can crushed tomatoes\\\",\\n    \\\"1/2 cup vegetable broth\\\",\\n    \\\"1 tsp dried oregano\\\",\\n    \\\"1/2 tsp red pepper flakes (optional)\\\",\\n    \\\"Salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste\\\",\\n    \\\"1/4 cup fresh basil leaves, chopped, for garnish\\\"\\n  , \\\"2 tbsp nutritional yeast (optional, for a cheesy flavor)\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"instructions\\\": [\\n    \\\"Preheat your oven to 400\\\\ndeepF (200\\\\ndeepC).\\\",\\n    \\\"On a large baking sheet, toss the chopped bell pepper, zucchini, cherry tomatoes, red onion, and smashed garlic cloves with 2 tablespoons of olive oil, salt, and black pepper. Spread them in a single layer.\\\",\\n    \\\"Roast for 25-30 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender and slightly caramelized. Stir halfway through to ensure even roasting.\\\",\\n    \\\"While the vegetables are roasting, bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add the pasta and cook according to package dire